<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-478-636  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 478 636.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDN  August 3 1989 v34 n16 p145(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Icon lets software tools perform special tasks. (Icon programminglanguage; includes related article on Icon products)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wightman, Sandra L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>ICON, a very high-level programming language, has many specialfeatures that enable users to write complicated list-processingapplications quickly.andP;  It allows non-uniform control of iteration,performs data typing at runtime, and permits deeply-nestedexpressions through its 'success/failure' feature.andP;  Expressions'succeed' or 'fail' instead of returning Boolean values; anexpression that succeeds returns its right-hand side while anexpression that fails returns nothing.andP;  This feature avoids theneed for complicated series of conditional statements.andO;'Generator' operators manage iteration by letting the programevaluate the result of each operation and select whether toproceed to the next operation or break out of the loop.andP;  Icon alsohas many powerful facilities for processing data structures.andP;  Itsdisadvantages are lack of support and lack of modularity on somesystems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     String Processing LanguagesProgramming LanguagesSpecializationList Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>